What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend this course to anyone who wants to speak Chinese. If you are looking for an easy language credit this is not it.

I would recommend this class to a student; however, only if they are able to make this their top priority. Given the fact that I decided to take Chinese for fun and that I've been dealing with issues of mental health, etc., I was not able to perform as well as I could have. However, if a student has the time and energy to dedicate to this class more than they do to anything else -- they will certainly gain a lot from it.
I would recommend this course. Amazing teachers and is an effective way at learning Chinese.
